ally neglected negative theology that undergirds this apocalyptic tradition provides the key to a radically new view of apocalypse as at once religious and poetic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aApocalyptic literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aChristian poetryxHistory and criticism. 0aChristianity and literaturexHistory. 0aEpic poetryxHistory and criticism. 0aNegative theologyxChristianity. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804779739zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804779739423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804779739/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles